summary: One of the saddest things about GOT finishing to me will be the end of Sansa Stark’s storyline. Whilst I by far and large prefer...
body:
One of the saddest things about GOT finishing to me will be the end of Sansa Stark’s storyline. Whilst I by far and large prefer the book version, I’m not optimistic enough that the books will be completed and I’ll have to go on by what the show gives me as closure to Sansa’s arc.


It is saddening for me because, besides from being one of my favourite characters of all time and on a show/book that I’m heavily in love with (no matter how much the latest season sucked…) Sansa is a character I’ve always looked up to. From the young naive child that she was to somebody being forced to grow up before her time as the harsh realities of the real world hit her, her journey has honestly been incredible.


Seeing the changes and the maturity, the growth… it was all fucking awesome. And the reason it made a big impact upon me is that I see it as a metaphor to life. That is the beauty of all “coming in age” stories. The child grew up and acquired strengths over the years like we all do.


Arya and Bran’s stories also have this, and I love them too. Sansa’s resonates with me more however because hers is more based on reality (as much as it can be) and because I saw a lot of myself in her younger self before she was forced to grow up; whereas Arya and Bran’s stories do have magical elements and the former deals with themes of war. Something I’ve not experienced myself thankfully.


So free cheers to Sansa Stark, a character I’ll never forget no matter how many books I’ve read or shows and movies I watch.

summary:
Try n' Hold me Back - Rob Bailey + The Hustle Standard 
“Our gods are quiet... but when they move, they uproot...
body:
The Burnt World: 32 - The She-Wolves of Winterfell

Try n’ Hold me Back - Rob Bailey + The Hustle Standard 

“Our gods are quiet… but when they move, they uproot everything” 

Excerpt: 

“And why am I here, Ma’am?” She folds her hands behind her back. Shifting her feet shoulder length apart. At-Ease. A proper soldier.

“An excellent question, Ms. Stark. Why are you here?” The princess turns her delicate frame square with hers.

“Are you here because of your friend, Howland Reed? A wise young man who speaks so highly of the daughter of winterfell. A gentle man who calls you his hero because you fought his bullies for him when you were young.”

Her ears turn hot from the memory. It was at the Summer Solstice festival, just after her nameday. The Umbers were beating him up and calling him frog eater and swamp rat. She punched greatJon so hard he broke his nose.

“Are you here because ‘Starks serve their country?’ Because you have been denied that opportunity… despite your skill and talent. Denied the opportunity to have Honor and Glory of your own.”

It sounds selfish when its said like that. Petty. Stupid. No… She swallows hard. Men are allowed to seek Honor and Glory. Why can’t she? Why should she be denied her own ambition? No. It’s not petty.

“Are you here because you are running away from your brute of a betrothed? Because you can’t stomach the thought of being forced to be his wife? Because you want to retch when you think of him rutting into you? Using you until he’s bored and then proceeding to destroy what’s left of your honor with his exploits? With… ‘making the eight’ as he calls it?”

Behind them Captain Dayne shuffles uncomfortably.

“…Aye Ma’am,” she answers. “All of it an’ more”

body:
Bran: You were stabbed. Do you remember anything?

Arya: Only the ambulance ride to the hospital.

Robb: That wasn’t an ambulance. I drove you.

Arya: But I heard a siren.

Bran: That was Sansa.

Sansa: I’m sorry, I got nervous.

description:
Arya grew up sheltered in the Ark with her four siblings, so when she comes down to Earth she’s ready to discover a new world, and she ends up finding a new best friend, Gendry.

Fill for Arya and Gendry Week 2018

The bunker chapter, people!! It’s been almost six years since they have been underground and maybe it’s time for Arya and Gendry to stop dancing around each other :)

This suffered a few changes after “The Dark Year”, because I couldn’t help myself, but still lighter that what actually happened them.

And this one very much more Arya and Gendry focused - so ENJOY!!

(Also an hint of what I wanted of Kane and Abby in the flashbacks…)

Also at FFN!!!

summary:
🐺 Arya Stark appreciation 20/- 

  But it was Jon Snow she thought of most. She wished somehow they could come to the Wall...
caption:
🐺 Arya Stark appreciation 20/-

But it was Jon Snow she thought of most. She wished somehow they could come to the Wall before Winterfell, so Jon might muss up her hair and call her “little sister.” She’d tell him, “I missed you,” and he’d say it too at the very same moment, the way they always used to say things together. She would have liked that. 

She would have liked that better than anything.
